                     <interp inst="t18241028-85-person803" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . A curtain and a wash-hand bason were stolen from the house on the 4th of October; I had seen them safe at ten o'clock the night before. I went to bed about twenty minutes past ten, and got up at seven in the morning, The curtain and basin had been in the wash-house; the sheets and shirts were in the yard - the fence of the yard is higher than the wash-house; the wash-house door was broken open, and the bolt forced. I had not seen the prisoner about the premises. I have not seen any of the property since.</p>
               <p>SARAH LAMBOURNE. I live at Mr. 
